[[File:N-400.pdf|thumb|USCIS Form N-400, Application for Naturalization (2016 revision)]]'''Form N-400''' is used to apply for [[Citizenship of the United States|US citizenship]] through the [[naturalization]] process. [[Permanent residence (United States)|Lawful permanent residents]] (also known as green card holders) of the United States, who meet the eligibility requirements, can file N-400 form to request citizenship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uscis.gov/n-400 |title=Application for Naturalization &#124; USCIS |publisher=Uscis.gov |date= |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref> In the United States, 8.8 million Lawful Permanent Residents are eligible to naturalize.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2015/05/prweb12693392.htm|title=MyNaturalization.com, an Affordable Solution for US Naturalization|date=|publisher=Prweb.com|accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref>
Becoming an American citizen gives the same rights and privileges of citizenship as [[Natural-born-citizen clause|natural born American citizens]], except one : naturalized U.S. citizens are not eligible for the Office of the President of the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uscis.gov/sites/default/files/USCIS/Office%20of%20Citizenship/Citizenship%20Resource%20Center%20Site/Publications/PDFs/G-1151.pdf|title=National Customer Service Center|publisher=Uscis.gov|format=PDF|accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref>
==US citizenship eligibility requirements== To be able to apply for citizenship through naturalization, you have to meet the following requirements.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uscis.gov/us-citizenship/citizenship-through-naturalization|title=How to Apply for Naturalization|website=USCIS|access-date=2016-06-14}}</ref> You must: * Be 18 years of age or above. * Be a lawful permanent resident for 5 years (3 years if married to a US citizen). * Have maintained continuous residence during the past 5 years (3 years if married to a US citizen). * Have maintained physical presence during the past 5 years (3 years if married to a US citizen). * Have good moral character. * Have basic knowledge of [[English language|English]]. * Have basic knowledge of [[Federal government of the United States|US government]] and [[History of the United States|history]]. * Be willing to take the [[Oath of Allegiance (United States)|Oath of Allegiance]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uscis.gov/sites/default/files/files/form/n-400instr.pdf|format=PDF|title=Instructions for Application for Naturalization|publisher=Uscis.gov|accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref>
==Content== The N-400 form is a series of questions about eligibility, personal information, marital history, children, criminal activities and the oath of allegiance to the United States. Many services, on the web, help candidates to the naturalization to fill the form. Sometimes, a lawyer's help is required.
Filing the form costs $640 along with a $85 biometric fee for a total of $725, where applicable. Exceptions can be seen on the federal website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uscis.gov/n-400|title=Application for Naturalization &#124; USCIS|date=|publisher=Uscis.gov|accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref>
After filing the form, the applicant undergoes an interview process with the [[United States Citizenship and Immigration Services]] (USCIS). The USCIS interview includes an English and civics test. The English test has three components: reading, writing, and speaking. The civics test covers important U.S. history and government topics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uscis.gov/citizenship/learners/study-test |title=Study for the Test &#124; USCIS |publisher=Uscis.gov |date= |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref>
