'''Targeted surveillance''' (or '''targeted interception''') is a form of [[surveillance]] that is targeted on specific persons of interest and distinguished from [[mass surveillance]] (or bulk interception). Untargeted surveillance is routinely accused of treating innocent people as suspects in ways that are unfair, of violating [[human rights]], international treaties and conventions as well as national laws<ref>
