* {{cite web|last1=Simon|first1=Joel|title=Why Mass Surveillance Violates International Law|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/news_and_politics/foreigners/2015/06/mass_surveillance_violates_international_law_david_kaye_s_report_to_the.html|publisher=Slate|accessdate=2 January 2017|date=17 June 2015}}
* {{cite web|title=The Members States may not impose a general obligation to retain data on providers of electronic communications services|url=http://curia.europa.eu/jcms/upload/docs/application/pdf/2016-12/cp160145en.pdf|publisher=Court of Justice of the European Union|accessdate=2 January 2017}}
* {{cite web|last1=Dunn|first1=John E.|title=Government’s "general and indiscriminate" data collection ruled unlawful|url=https://nakedsecurity.sophos.com/2016/12/22/governments-general-and-indiscriminate-data-collection-ruled-unlawful/|publisher=Naked Security|accessdate=2 January 2017|date=22 December 2016}}
* {{cite web|last1=McCarthy|first1=Kieren|title=European human rights court rules mass surveillance illegal|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2016/01/20/human_rights_court_rules_mass_surveillance_illegal/|publisher=The Register}}
